- !<Text/6f5b5d7d-295d-4cf3-9873-d19b7287eee4>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: Text
  Enabled: true
  RenderOrder: 0
  StretchMode: Stretch
  VerticalAlignment: Top
  HorizontalAlignment: Left
  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |
    Slide 10.  Editor Button Icons - Focus on the Preview Window 
     [Show Preview]
    
    > Let’s go a little deeper in understanding this view because it’s quite foundational
    
    On the top left corner 
    
    > Interactive Preview - Is the one we just clicked on, to enable the spatial representation of your preview background and test your experiences. 
    
    On the top center 
    
    > Check out the “Interactive Preview Window”, select your favorite “Interactive Preview” and check out how your game preview changes. 
    
    On the top right corner 
    
    > Check out the Reset  Icon  - Generally used to refresh the preview and check the changes, this should also be happening by default after compilation.
    
    > Check out the Settings Icon - where we can  change a number of properties for our preview, including setting the simulation as "Fullscreen Spectacle Simulation”.
    
     On the bottom 
    
    > Check out the start / custom location dropdown: Allows you to reset the position of the camera and scene elements. 

  Editable: false
  ShowEditingPreview: true
