  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |
    This asset allows you to easily create your cusotom Teleprompter Lens
    
    1. Build and test the static mode with the placeholder images to understand how this works   2. You can interact with slides in many ways - moving your hands to hit the colliders (previous - left, next, - right) and press on the soft button collder to advance the presentation. You can also use the arrow button or the enable the mic button and saying loud "Previous" or "Next".  3. Repositon frame, change text per slides, import your own slides and swap the existing images. Reposition soft button colliders as you are more comfortable.   4. If adventurous, consider setting up the google integration on the local connection using websockets, that will allow you to update simultaneously a web viewer of the presentation and your lens. Start from copying outside of this project the webviewer example provided in the package.
    
    Please read the README.md for accessing informations in depth. 
    
    PS. This is an over simplification of the productionized Teleprompter you find in the Lens Explorer where you can access to your slides via Google Authentication.  

